Ad Text:
Data Analytics Manager
Full-Time | 2 Year Fixed Term | Sydney | $165,000 + 12% Super

About the Role

We are seeking an experienced Data Analytics Manager to lead a high-performing team and drive the delivery of advanced data and analytics capabilities across the arts and cultural sector.

This is an exciting opportunity to shape the organisation’s data strategy, optimise data pipelines and deliver insights that inform decision-making at the highest levels. You will oversee enterprise analytics architecture, mentor a skilled team and ensure best practice in data governance, engineering and analytics delivery.

Key Responsibilities

Lead and manage a data and analytics team, fostering continuous improvement and delivery excellence.
Oversee the development, optimisation and refinement of enterprise data models, pipelines, and metadata management.
Drive adoption of cloud-native solutions, leveraging Azure Synapse Analytics, Databricks and Azure DevOps.
Deliver advanced analytics and machine learning solutions that support strategic outcomes.
Ensure compliance with governance, security and regulatory standards.
Provide actionable insights and high-quality reporting to senior executives and stakeholders.
Monitor emerging trends in data engineering, analytics, AI/ML and advise on opportunities for adoption.
 
About You

To succeed in this role you will bring:

Proven experience in data engineering, information management or analytics leadership.
Strong track record leading teams delivering cloud-native data solutions.
Technical expertise in Azure Synapse Analytics, Databricks and Azure DevOps.
Experience with enterprise data modelling, data warehousing and analytics architecture.
Ability to translate technical concepts into business value for non-technical stakeholders.
Strong influencing and stakeholder management skills.
Excellent communication and problem-solving abilities.

Desirable:

Tertiary qualifications in a relevant field.
Experience delivering AI initiatives in business or the public sector.
Consulting or advisory experience.
 
What’s on Offer

In addition to a competitive salary of $165,000 + 12% superannuation, you will enjoy:

Hybrid work model - 2 days from home and 3 days on site in Sydney.
Flexible working hours to balance personal and professional life.
Additional paid leave between Christmas and New Year.
Paid cultural leave to observe personal religious or cultural obligations.
Access to wellbeing programs, corporate discounts and a holistic Employee Assistance Program for you, your family and kin.

How to Apply

If you are a data leader passionate about driving impact through analytics and information management and want to make a real difference in the arts and cultural sector, we encourage you to apply. Reach out to Lee Bartlett for more information - lee@bluefinresources.com.au

Based at Knoxfield (moving to Mulgrave in May, 2026)
Full time permanent position
Great team and work environment

Purpose

To operationalise data governance across the organisation’s analytics environment—ensuring data is accurate, secure, well-defined, and responsibly managed. The role translates policy into practice across tools like Informatica, Azure Data Factory, Databricks, dbt, and BI platforms.

Key Responsibilities

Framework Enablement: Translate policies into practical tools and coordinate governance forums
Metadata & Cataloguing: Curate glossaries, drive lineage/classifications, maintain tagging conventions
Data Quality Management: Define and automate DQ rules, monitor SLAs, triage issues
Integration & Transformation Controls: Apply governance in Informatica, ADF, Databricks, dbt
Risk, Privacy & Compliance: Conduct PIAs, ensure APPs compliance
Change & Training: Create playbooks, run enablement sessions
Reporting: Maintain governance scorecards and domain health reports

Key Competencies, Skills and Qualifications

Tertiary degree in Information Systems, Data/Computer Science or equivalent
Desirable certifications: Azure, Databricks, dbt, Informatica, Collibra, IAPP
3–6 years in data governance/data quality
Hands-on with at least two of: Informatica, Azure Data Factory, Databricks, dbt
Strong SQL and data modelling knowledge
Experience with data catalogs (Purview, Collibra, Alation) and lineage tools
Proven DQ automation and privacy/security understanding
Excellent stakeholder engagement skills

What PFD is Offering the Successful Candidate

We are offering competitive remuneration, superannuation and other staff benefits (such as discounts on staff purchases, discounted accommodation, health insurance and banking).

Please submit your application (cover letter and resume) via the apply now link below

As part of our recruitment process, do you agree to undertake employment checks? These checks may include a medical assessment (including a drug and alcohol test), National Police History Check, Working With Children/Vulnerable Groups Check, Licence Validation/Demerit Point Check.

Please note: We do not accept unsolicited CV's from Recruitment agencies / third parties and we will not be liable or responsible for any fees or costs associated with unsolicited CV's sent directly to Line Managers.

About the Company

Our client is a global leader with a powerhouse portfolio of household-name brands, trusted across homes, schools and workplaces. With strong local operations backed by an international parent group, they continue to expand across ANZ and offer a collaborative, high-performing culture.

As FP&A Manager, you’ll lead the ANZ financial planning and analysis function. This is a hands-on leadership role where you’ll take ownership of reporting, budgeting, and forecasting while delivering commercial insights to support business growth.

Key Responsibilities Include:

Leading ANZ FP&A reporting, planning and forecasting cycles;
Delivering actionable insights to senior stakeholders;

Advanced SAP ERP and BI systems knowledge; and
CPA or CA qualification (preferred).

$160,000 + Super;
Western Sydney location with onsite parking;
Career growth with a global portfolio of consumer brands; and
Collaborative, innovative environment.

Melbourne is Australia's fastest growing city - a city that is becoming increasingly reliant on public transport networks. Since 2009, Metro proudly continues to operate and maintain a world-class train service and network through to delivering significant transport projects that will shape how Melbourne moves. With Zero Harm at the foundation of everything we do, we want everyone to get home safely. We are one team, helping to connect and shape a better Melbourne.





The Business Analyst is responsible for the development of contractual claims and variations, in line with the OCMS franchise module contractual obligations. You will be involved in the end-to-end process of claims, including data collection across multiple functions and assets and financial modelling, to the submission to the Department of Transport.

Reporting to the OCMS Contractual Claims Manager the Business Analyst will collaborate across internal teams to collect the necessary information and develop and utilise financial models to present and submit variations claims to the Department of Transport to reach commercial outcomes.

This is a 2 year opportunity located in Docklands at our Head Office

KEY RESPONSIBILITIES

Complete analysis and documentation to support OCMS strategic priorities
Engage key stakeholders across the team, division, and broader organisation to collate the required information for claims.
Support the development of variation claims, including contractual and financial analysis and validation of technical asset details
Complete financial modelling to prepare contractual claims and variations for submission.
Collect and manipulate data from various sources to compile into the necessary frameworks required for submission to the Department of Transport and Planning (DTP)
Engage with Project Management and Engineering teams to collect the artefacts required for the retention submission
Liaise with internal finance teams and DTP to ensure the accuracy and the timely completion of the retention submission
Maintaining and updating forecasts and actuals as claims are completed.

ABOUT YOU

Tertiary qualification in Business or Financial Management
Ability to analyse data and write and present reports, undertake and complete complex tasks
Ability to communicate to staff at all levels (verbal & written)
Familiarity and knowledge of key accounting concepts.
Experience with the preparation and collation of financial information and project management methodologies is desirable.
Financial modelling experience
Knowledge of technology assets, asset lifecycle preferred.
Advanced proficiency in Microsoft Excel.
Familiarity with VBA, macros, Power Query and Power BI integration.

NEXT STEPS

If this role resonates with your values, experience, and career needs, then come join us and help connect people and places for a growing Melbourne!

Don't meet every single requirement? As an inclusive and diverse workplace, we encourage all applicants to apply. Applications close Sunday 12th October 2025.

Metro is committed to making reasonable adjustments to provide a positive, barrier-free recruitment process for candidates with specific access needs. Candidates who require adjustments are encouraged to declare this in their application, so that the contact person for the position can discuss your needs.





WHY WORK AT METRO?

Work for a multi-award-winning rail operator with rewarding career opportunities that provide you with the support and training to take your career to the next level!
Be part of an inclusive, diverse, and supportive company made up of various backgrounds, cultures, and experiences.
Work-life balance options including flexible working arrangements, 14 weeks paid parental leave, and purchasing up to 4 weeks of additional leave per year.
All eligible Metro employees receive a free Myki Pass that allows free Public Transport in Victoria.
Access to a wide range of corporate discounts including healthcare, fitness, finance, and more.

Company Description

About SEEK

SEEK’s portfolio of diverse businesses make a positive impact on a truly global scale. Our purpose is to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives and help organisations succeed. We create world-class technology solutions to connect more people to relevant employment, education, small business and volunteer opportunities. We have a culture of high-performance in our workplaces and celebrate the diversity of our employees who contribute to the success of our organisation.

Life at SEEK

SEEK’s purpose is at the centre of everything we do. Our SEEK, which defines the way we work, is all about what makes us unique and a little bit different. Passion, Team, Delivery and Future are our principles that drive innovation and creativity. SEEK strives to support employee wellbeing by providing an amazing experience at work which led us to being named AFR BOSS Top 10 Best Places to Work in Technology (2021-2024). We are proud to work in an environment that's inclusive where everyone's unique ideas, experiences and perspectives are valued.

Our award-winning head office in Cremorne (just a 4 min walk from Richmond station) provides an exceptional space to collaborate with colleagues. The building provides sweeping views of the city, a games area, sit and stand desks at every workstation, modern end-of-trip facilities and Thursday night drinks which gives our people an opportunity to connect in a social setting.

Job Description

Help Shape the Future of Data at SEEK

At SEEK, we’re on a mission to help people live more fulfilling and productive working lives. In our Technology and AI teams, data is at the heart of that mission – powering smarter decisions, powering AI innovation, and creating product experiences that truly matter.

As a Solution Architect in our Data & AI domain, you’ll be a trusted thought leader and hands‑on partner, helping to set the direction for SEEK’s data platforms and ensuring our solutions deliver measurable business and customer value. This is your opportunity to work alongside some of the best in the industry, within a collaborative, high‑trust environment that values curiosity, innovation, and continuous learning.

About the role

You will sit at the intersection of technology strategy and delivery execution – working across SEEK’s Technology and AI teams to translate big aspirations into actionable architecture roadmaps and pragmatic solutions. Your role blends deep technical expertise with influence, governance, and leadership in the data architecture space.

What you’ll be doing

Shape the vision – Define and evolve SEEK’s architecture strategy and roadmaps for data, analytics, and AI solutions.
Lead with impact – Champion architectural best practice to ensure all data solutions are robust, scalable, and aligned with SEEK standards.
Enable autonomy – Establish guardrails and principles that empower teams to make aligned technology decisions.
Work with delivery teams – Collaborate closely with engineers and data specialists to influence design and operational best practice.
Explore what’s next – Research and assess new technologies, recommending adoption where they deliver value.
Protect the business – Identify architectural risks early and recommend effective mitigation strategies.
Connect and influence – Communicate complex architectural decisions clearly to both technical and non‑technical audiences.

About the team

You’ll join SEEK’s high‑performing Architecture function of 25+ professionals spanning six key domains: Enterprise, Customer, Data & AI, Platform, Growth, and Architecture Practices. Your focus will be within Data & AI Architecture, supporting Data Services, AI Analytics, and SEEK’s broader AI‑powered ambitions. We’re collaborative, outcome‑focused, and love solving big, complex problems that make a difference for millions of users.

Qualifications

Technical expertise

Extensive experience in data architecture – including modelling, warehousing, lakes, ETL/ELT, and modern data platforms.
Strong knowledge of batch/real‑time processing, event‑driven designs, and building scalable pipelines across mixed database environments.
Experience with analytics platforms, visualisation tools, and integrating ML capabilities for advanced analytics.
Proven expertise in data governance – frameworks, catalogues, lineage, metadata, privacy‑by‑design, classification, and access control.
Background in enterprise integration and data management – including interoperability, federation, MDM, and data quality improvement.

Personal skills

Strategic vision – Balance big‑picture thinking with practical delivery.
Collaborative mindset – Work well across tech and business domains.
Problem‑solving – Break down complexity into actionable steps.
Continuous learner – Adapt quickly and stay ahead in a changing tech landscape.
Influential communicator – Engage, motivate, and influence stakeholders at all levels.
Outcome‑driven – Consistently focus on delivering business value.
Additional Information

Permanent Perks
At SEEK we offer:

Annual Performance Bonus Plan
Support of flexible working, including a mix of office and work from home days depending on your role.
Paid and unpaid leave benefits including Personal Flexi Days and Volunteer Days, as well as the opportunity to purchase additional leave

At SEEK, we are passionate about fostering a culture of inclusion and wellbeing that embraces and values the diversity of our people. We are a purpose driven business that works with heart.

We know teams with diverse ideas, experiences and perspectives are more creative and are critical to ensuring effective delivery and innovating to enable our future success. As such, we welcome applications from people with diverse backgrounds and life experiences, especially as they relate to gender, sexual identity, culture, faith, disability and life stages. If you have the skills, curiosity and an adaptable mindset but don't meet every responsibility or qualification listed in this advertisement, please still get in touch with us.

Should you require any specific support or adjustments throughout the recruitment process and beyond, please advise us and we will be happy to assist.

For this role, only those candidates with the eligible right to work will be considered.

SEEK kindly requests no unsolicited resumes or approaches from recruitment agencies and will not be responsible for any associated fees.

Job Title: Head of Data Governance, Privacy and Regulatory Analytics
Ad Text:
Unique, highly visible role, working with a well-regarded executive leadership team.
Excellent work life balance and a real opportunity to have immediate impact
Sydney Based. Up to $250k base + super + Benefits
About the Role:

We are seeking a Head of Data Governance, Privacy, and Regulatory Analytics to lead and shape the organisation’s approach to regulatory data strategy, privacy frameworks, and governance. This is a pivotal leadership role in a highly data-driven environment, working closely with regulators and senior stakeholders to ensure compliance while driving innovation and efficiency.

Key Responsibilities:

Regulatory Data Strategy: Develop and implement strategies to meet regulatory requirements, including Economic and Financial Statistics (EFS) reporting and Open Banking compliance.
Regulator Engagement: Build and maintain strong relationships with regulatory bodies such as APRA, ASIC ACCC and OAIC, ensuring accurate and transparent communication.
Data Governance Leadership: Establish and maintain frameworks for data ownership, lineage, and retention, ensuring the integrity and quality of critical data elements (CDEs).
Privacy Oversight: Manage first-line privacy responsibilities, including Privacy Impact Assessments and embedding privacy by design into business processes.
Cross-Team Collaboration: Partner with risk, compliance, and technology teams to deliver integrated data solutions aligned with regulatory and business objectives.
Continuous Improvement: Stay ahead of evolving regulatory requirements, driving innovation and efficiency in data systems and reporting processes.
What We’re Looking For:

We’re seeking a dynamic leader with a strong regulatory focus, technical expertise, and the ability to bridge the gap between data systems and compliance.

Proven leadership in data governance within financial services, including managing CDEs, data lineage, and retention.
Extensive experience in regulatory reporting, particularly EFS and Open Banking standards.
Strong technical understanding of data systems and architecture.
Demonstrated success in engaging with regulators and representing organisational positions.
Hands-on experience with privacy frameworks, including Privacy Impact Assessments.
Exceptional communication skills to translate complex regulatory requirements for diverse audiences.
Strategic thinker with the ability to anticipate regulatory changes and their implications.
Relevant industry qualifications/professional certifications in risk management or compliance.
Ready to Apply?

If you’re a data-driven professional with a passion for regulatory compliance, privacy, and governance, we’d love to hear from you. This is your chance to make a significant impact in a challenging and rewarding leadership role.
This role offers a unique blend of technical, regulatory, and leadership challenges. If you’re ready to take on this exciting opportunity, apply now!
For a confidential chat, contact Jen Jones at Ink Recruitment on +61 (0)409 926 897.

Provide data-driven insights to support strategic decisions across sales, marketing, and product development.

Job Title: Senior Investment Analytics and Insights Analyst
Ad Text:
About Cbus
 
Created by workers, for workers, Cbus Super is one of Australia’s most successful Superannuation funds. For almost four decades we’ve proudly represented those who help shape Australia, hard-working individuals who deserve to make the most of their retirement, no matter the industry. As an award-winning fund we’ve been recognised for the benefits provided to our members and our innovative investment approach.  All while staying committed to our member first ethos as a proud Industry Fund.
 
About the role
 
The Senior Investment Analytics and Insights Analyst is pivotal in driving the fund’s digital transformation and enhancing investment decision making. Reporting to the Manager, Investment Insights & Reporting you will support the investment team by delivering data-driven insights and sophisticated analytics through business intelligence tools, enabling a whole-of-fund perspective on performance and risk.
 
The ideal candidate will bring expertise in integrating diverse data sources, building insightful dashboards and working within multi-asset environments. Your deep understanding of investment data and systems will ensure that key metrics are monitored effectively, making this role essential to optimising investment outcomes and strategic fund management.
 
Key Accountabilities

Design and deliver data-driven analytics solutions by collaborating with stakeholders to understand reporting needs
Develop and maintain PowerBI dashboards and data workflows using SQL and data modelling to optimize reporting and insights
Enhance and automate existing reporting processes replacing manual Excel models with scalable data-driven solutions
Support data governance initiatives, including documentation, glossaries and integration with governance tools
Provide training and collaborate across teams to improve data literacy, share knowledge and support long term analytics capabilities
What will you bring?

Experience in a similar Data Analyst or Analytics and Insights Analyst role specifically working with multi asset Investment Data
Strong expertise in SQL, data modeling and building reusable data assets using tools like Excel or Python
Effective communicator and collaborator with experience working across complex stakeholder environments
Proactive and accountable with a focus on automating processes and improving data quality and governance
Knowledge of third-party investment systems such as Factset, Ortec, Pearl, BarraOne, RIMES, Datastream and/or Bloomberg preferred
Exposure to using Microsoft Azure, including managing cloud-based data solutions and supporting platform integration
Belong at Cbus
 
We value difference, and embrace people with diverse backgrounds, experiences, gender identities, abilities and thinking styles. We believe that, with diversity of perspectives and experiences, you get better teams and outcomes. We’re looking for people of all genders, races, nationalities, orientations and of all abilities to join us.
 
We’re keen to hear from you
 
If you've read through the requirements of this role and you feel like you haven’t fully met the criteria, we would still encourage you to apply. We're aware of accessibility barriers when it comes to applying for a job and we want to help. If you require assistance with your application, please contact our Talent Acquisition Team via careers@cbussuper.com.au 
 
Like to know more about working with Cbus? Listen to some of our videos with members of the Cbus team on our website, cbussuper.com.au/careers
 
Applications Close: Tuesday 14 October 2025 
 
This is a full-time position based in Melbourne
 
Agencies, please note: All Cbus vacancies are managed by our internal Talent Acquisition Team.  Should external assistance be required we will reach out to our preferred agency partners, Thank you.

About us

From humble roots in Eromanga, QLD, we’ve been fuelling the furthest corners of Australia for over 40 years. But we think the most exciting journey’s still on the horizon.

Joining IOR puts you in the driver’s seat. You'll get the opportunity to own your ambition and build a worthwhile career - all while seeing your impact on the faces of your team and the communities we serve. You won't see our logo on racing cars, but you will be part of a team that helps fuel LifeFlight's choppers.

Whether you’re driving trucks, designing tech, manufacturing tanks or managing logistics behind the scenes, a career with IOR means going further, in every sense of the word - in your relationships, your impact and your remarkable career.

Right team

Work with people you trust and form relationships that will go the distance
Build something great with a team that will have a laugh and have your back

Right Track

So many career opportunities to explore... and you’re in the driver’s seat
Grow with us at IOR - the bigger we get, the bigger your opportunities become

Right Now

We want you to succeed, so you’re given trust and autonomy to do what it takes
Real momentum, real impact and the sense that there’s plenty more to come

About your role,

We are looking for a highly skilled and motivated Senior Data Scientist to join our growing team at IOR. This role plays a critical part in building a world-class data capability to enhance commercial decision-making, drive margin expansion, and improve operational efficiency. You will work closely with leadership and business teams to design advanced analytics models, unlock insights, and develop tools that power everyday business decisions.

Accelerate enterprise value by embedding performance analytics, pricing intelligence, and data-driven strategy to drive growth and optimise margins.
Embed advanced analytics at scale through machine learning, automation, and scenario modelling to inform operations, strategy, and commercial outcomes.
Elevate pricing performance with custom pricing frameworks driven by market data, operational systems, and IOR’s proprietary Dashboard platform.
Deliver strategic insights by translating complex data into simple, actionable recommendations that influence leadership decisions and operational execution.
Uplift analytical maturity by developing scalable tools, mentoring analysts, and collaborating with tech teams to enhance IOR’s data architecture and capability.

About you

To succeed in this role, you will need the following attributes:

Educational foundation in Data Science, Mathematics, Computer Science, Engineering, or a related discipline (Bachelor’s or Master’s required).
Proven technical expertise in supervised machine learning, statistical modelling, simulations, and advanced programming (Python, R, SQL).
Strong analytical capabilities with experience in large-scale data visualisation, real-time analytics, and cloud infrastructure (preferably Azure).
Experience in advanced analytics, with added value for backgrounds in Monte Carlo simulation, predictive pricing, and supply chain optimisation.
Commercially focused mindset, blending Agile practices with the ability to link analytical outputs to business performance and mentor others.

Why join IOR?

You can feel it from day one. The energy, the growth… the sense that this place is going somewhere. And you're not just along for the ride. You’re behind the wheel.

IOR’s the kind of place where you put your name to a project, and you own it. The wins, the challenges, and everything in between we back you to see it through, even when things don’t go to plan. Support is always there if you need it. Otherwise, you’re trusted to do what it takes to keep things running.

You don’t get that in too many places.

Approaching each day through our values of Innovation finding solutions, Our Communities serving people, and Reliability getting results, our team is focused on delivering what really matters to our customers. It’s this mindset that drives us forward.

The best part? As we grow bigger, the opportunities get bigger, too. Backed by a solid strategy and a right to win, joining our team means more projects, more challenges, and more chances to stretch yourself.

What does this mean for you?

Be part of an unbeatable culture where people really do enjoy coming to work
Investment in your career through training and development programs, ongoing support, plus the backing to take your career in whichever direction you choose
Work hard, play hard with our Blue Squad - trivias, barbecues and plenty of laughs!

Contribute to the evolution of Elysium’s consulting methodologies.

Can align data and technology strategies with business outcomes.

Possess functional or technical knowledge of platforms such as Fabric, Databricks, Snowflake, Tableau.
Are skilled in stakeholder engagement and executive-level communication.
Can translate complex technical concepts into clear, strategic recommendations.

Hold or are eligible for an AGSVA security clearance.

Your expertise will be crucial in integrating diverse systems and streamlining processes, enabling smooth transitions, scalable operations, and future-ready supply chain capabilities.

What's in it for you?

Competitive salary package
Flexible work arrangements to support work-life balance
An exciting opportunity to shape the development of innovative solutions across ‘s Group Supply Chain.

A range of fantastic Ventia employee benefits, including discounted private health insurance, paid parental leave, discounted travel, and more!

Key Responsibilities

Supply Chain Strategy & Solution Design

Lead the design and implementation of supply chain solutions that prioritize access to information and are aligned with business objectives, supplier capabilities, and system limitations.

Ensure supply chain solutions are aligned with broader business transformation initiatives and the organization's technology roadmap.

Project Leadership & Execution

Manage the full project lifecycle—from scoping and planning through to execution and post-implementation review.
Lead cross-functional project teams, ensuring clearly defined roles, responsibilities, and accountability.
Proactively identify and mitigate risks related to transitioning technical environments and supplier dependencies.

Data-Driven Decision Making

Utilize advanced analytics to evaluate supply chain performance, identify inefficiencies, and anticipate future demand.
Design and implement reporting tools that deliver actionable insights to senior leadership.
Translate complex data into clear, strategic recommendations that enhance business agility and resilience.

Stakeholder Engagement & Change Leadership

Collaborate closely with key internal stakeholders—particularly in supply chain, finance, and project teams—to co-develop effective solutions.
Facilitate workshops and design sessions to align on priorities, define solution pathways, and build consensus.
Lead change management initiatives to drive the successful adoption of new systems, processes, and ways of working.

Could You Be Our Senior Supply Chain Solutions Lead?

Hold extensive experience in supply chain strategy, project execution, or supplier enablement.
Demonstrated success in navigating complex and evolving technical environments.
Strong proficiency in ERP systems such as SAP or Oracle (critical), with experience in data analytics tools like Power BI or Tableau, and working knowledge of SQL (preferred).
Professional certification in Project Management (e.g., PMP, PRINCE2) or Lean Six Sigma is advantageous.
Background in solution architecture or large-scale supply chain transformation initiatives.
Excellent communication, negotiation, and stakeholder management capabilities.
Proven ability to lead through ambiguity and deliver results in fast-paced, dynamic settings.
Bachelor's degree in Supply Chain, Business, Engineering, or a related field is beneficial.
